integer entries). TwoLineArray[{a1, a2, ..., a n}, {b1, b2, ..., b n}] \
returns the generalized permutation matrix corresponding to the two-line \
array. TwoLineArray[{b1, b2, ..., bn}] is equivalent to TwoLineArray[{1, 2, \
..., n}, {b1, b2, ..., bn}].", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
